oc:kn_0e971561 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When auditing, documenting, or extending any design system component" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Consistency over creativity — the system exists so teams don't reinvent the wheel. Components should be composable, not rigid. Flexibility within constraints is the goal." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Design systems derive their value from consistency; diverging from established patterns undermines the entire system's purpose." .

oc:kn_4ea6cf68 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When extending or modifying existing components" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Breaking changes need migration paths. Version and migrate all changes to the design system." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without migration paths, breaking changes cause downstream failures across all consuming applications." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_55937cb9 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When managing a design system end-to-end" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Audit the full system (naming consistency, token coverage, component completeness) 2. Document components (variants, props, states, accessibility, do's/don'ts) 3. Extend with new patterns (identify gap, check existing patterns, propose design with tokens)" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_d24190d8 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When beginning any design system work" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Start with an audit before extending. Know where you are before deciding where to go. Prioritize coverage over perfection — 80% of components documented beats 100% of 10." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Auditing establishes a baseline; broad coverage ensures the system is actually useful across the product." .

oc:kn_fce73aa8 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When documenting components or reviewing system completeness" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If it's not documented, it doesn't exist. Every component must have documented variants, states, sizes, behavior, and accessibility notes." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Undocumented components cannot be adopted consistently by teams, leading to fragmentation and duplication." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

